{{Infobox company | name = Books4cars | logo = Books4cars logo.png | type = Corp. | genre = | fate = | predecessor = | successor = | foundation = 1997 | founder = Alex Voss | defunct = | location_city = [[Seattle, Washington]] | location_country = | location = | locations = | area_served = global, via web; [[Seattle, Washington]]area via storefront | key_people = | industry = Rare, new and used automotive and motorcycle books | products = | production = | services = Online shopping, book search | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | aum = | assets = | equity = | owner = Alex Voss | num_employees = | parent = | divisions = | subsid = | homepage = {{URL|http://www.books4cars.com/}} | footnotes = | intl = }}
'''Books4cars''' is a web-based company in [[Seattle, Washington]], that carries used and rare books related to cars, trucks and motorcycles, such as service manuals, owners manuals and historical books. The business was started in 1997 in [[Detroit]], [[Michigan]], from a home collection of books by automotive engineer and mechanic Alex Voss. Books4cars relocated to Seattle's [[Columbia City, Seattle|Columbia City]] neighborhood in 2000.
