[[File:Gustave_Courbet_033.jpg|thumb]]
'''''Portrait of Charles Baudelaire''''' is a portrait of the poet [[Charles Baudelaire]] by [[Gustave Courbet]]. The artist himself dated it to 1840, but it seems to have mostly been painted around 1847, a year in which the poet and the painter met frequently. It was shown in the Courbet Pavilion at the 1855 [[Exposition Universelle (1855)|Exposition Universelle]] and was bought four years later by the publisher [[Auguste Poulet-Malassis]], who then nominally sold it to [[Charles Asselineau]] on 15 June 1862 to prevent it being seized. [[Alfred Bruyas]] acquired it for 3000 francs and in 1876 gave it to the [[Musée Fabre]] in Montpellier, where it still hangs.

